# No Cursor co-author on commits

- Never add `Co-authored-by: Cursor` (or `cursoragent@cursor.com`, or any Cursor co-author trailer) to commit messages.
- Commit author remains the repo user only (`pelishminer2-ui` / configured user.name).
- Do not amend or rewrite history solely to strip old Cursor trailers unless the user explicitly asks to purge history (that needs force-push).
- If Cursor IDE auto-appends a co-author trailer, strip it from the message before committing when you control the message text.
